    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>OpenIntro devotes significant space to normal probability tables and calculator use. We compute Z-scores and probabilities directly. The 68-95-99.7 rule (empirical rule) is the key heuristic for the normal distribution. For the Central Limit Theorem that justifies the normal's dominance, see Grinstead Ch. 9.</p>

